<!DOCTYPE tmc-service-paragraph SYSTEM "../dtd/paragraph-contents.dtd">
<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0309414"><name>ECD SYSTEM(w/o EGR System)</name><para id="RM10000000136K0" category="J"><dtccode/><dtcname>MIL Circuit</dtcname><subpara id="RM10000000136K0_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The MIL (Malfunction Indicator Lamp) is used to indicate vehicle malfunction detections by the ECM. When the ignition switch is turned to ON, power is supplied to the MIL circuit, and the ECM provides the circuit ground which illuminates the MIL.</ptxt><ptxt>The MIL operation can be checked visually. When the ignition switch is first turned to ON, the MIL should be illuminated and should then turn off when the engine is started. If the MIL remains illuminated or is not illuminated, conduct the following troubleshooting procedure using the GTS.</ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM10000000136K0_02" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="A403501E01" width="7.168479331in" height="3.812598425in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM10000000136K0_06" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM10000000136K0_06_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK THAT MIL IS ILLUMINATED</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Check the illumination condition of the MIL.</ptxt></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.34in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.34in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.40in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Illuminates → Turns off</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Ignition switch to ON → Engine is started</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>A</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Other than above</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>-</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>B</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="2-1"><actiontitle>CHECK FOR INTERMITTENT PROBLEMS</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM10000000136K6"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-2" childid="RM10000000136K0_06_0003"/></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136K0_06_0003" cellposition="2-2"><testtitle>CHECK CONNECTION BETWEEN GTS AND ECM</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS on.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Check the communication between the GTS and ECM.</ptxt><atten4><ptxt>It can be checked using the &quot;Engine&quot; item of the Data List.</ptxt></atten4></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="3.51in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="3.57in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Result</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Communication is possible</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>A</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Communication is not possible</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>B</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="3-2" childid="RM10000000136K0_06_0004"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-5"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-5"><actiontitle>GO TO VC OUTPUT CIRCUIT</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM10000000136JW"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136K0_06_0004" cellposition="3-2"><testtitle>CHECK WHETHER DTC OUTPUT RECURS</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS on.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Enter the following menus: Powertrain / Engine and ECT / Trouble Codes.</ptxt><gts-info category="dtc-read"><title>Powertrain &gt; Engine and ECT &gt; Trouble Codes</title><gts-exec function-id="50001"><gts-ecu ecu-id="61"/></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">0</app-param><app-param name="category-div">1</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Powertrain</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">61</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Engine and ECT</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">0</app-param><app-param name="selected-state">0</app-param></app-communication></gts-info></test1><test1><ptxt>Check if any DTCs have been detected. Note down any DTCs.</ptxt></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.96in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.12in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Result</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>DTCs are not output</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>A</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Any DTCs is output</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>B</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec><atten4><ptxt>Check for detected DTCs output from other ECUs which relate to the MIL.</ptxt></atten4></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="3-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="4-2" childid="RM10000000136K0_06_0005"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="3-4"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="4-4"><actiontitle>REPAIR CIRCUIT INDICATED BY OUTPUT DTC</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136K0_06_0005" cellposition="4-2"><testtitle>PERFORM ACTIVE TEST USING GTS</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS on.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Enter the following menus: Body Electrical / Combination Meter / Active Test / Check Engine Indicator.</ptxt><gts-info category="active-test"><title>Body Electrical &gt; Combination Meter &gt; Active Test</title><table type="active-test"><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Display</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="item-name" args1="150"><ptxt>Check Engine Indicator</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><gts-exec function-id="50004"><gts-ecu ecu-id="122"><gts-did did-id="150"/></gts-ecu></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">3</app-param><app-param name="catego